# Keeps public/ in the repository even while it holds no assets.
#
# Git does not track empty directories, and the Dockerfile copies this directory
# unconditionally (COPY --from=build /app/public ./public), so without a tracked
# file here a clean clone fails to build. Next.js also serves static assets from
# here by convention, so the directory is worth keeping rather than removing the
# COPY — a missing asset that silently never ships is a worse failure than a
# build error.
#
# robots.txt and sitemap.xml used to live here; they are now route handlers in
# src/app, because both need the deployment's own APP_URL at runtime.
